        -:   17:/***
        -:   18: This is the interface class for discrete tangent bundles, represented as a graph G_TB of nodes (tangent spaces) and edges (adjacency relations). This represents a d-dimensional tangent bundle.
        -:   19: Further structure is cycles around which holonomy is measured, and curvature is defined, and consequently one-rings of all edges around a single node.
        -:   20: The Tangent Bundle is "intrinsic" in the sense that the information required for designing fields does not require any embedding. The class includes variables that include embedding information like sources and normals (assuming the bundle is at most 1-codimensional).
        -:   21: They are however only used for input/output to the intrinsic variables.
        -:   22: ***/
